<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,151,535]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,367,392]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Diagnosis</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Thoracic pattern close to 
<taxonomicName box="[627,756,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beschkii">
<emphasis box="[627,756,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">H. beschkii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Machado" authorityYear="2006" box="[816,964,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luizfelipei">
<emphasis box="[816,964,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">H. luizfelipei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Figs. 32A,31E). Cercus in lateral view: dorsobasal expansion present. Ventrobasal expansion small but present occupying less than 1/3. Remainder almost straight (Fig. 16B). Cercus in mediodorsal view: apical portion very small, basal and medial portion subequal. Ventral expansion hairy. Medial process very wide triangular plate, external side with indentation; two sclerotized parallel ridges, one reaching tip of triangle, other reaching small step (Fig. 16A).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
